On 2009-05-22 07:36:12 -0700, Bart Schaefer wrote:
> I noticed while testing that always reloading has an additional benefit:
> You pick up changes in the SSH_AGENT environment.

I keep the SSH agent running until the last shell exits. So, this
is not a problem for me (except that I need to use login shells in
screen, but I've never noticed any drawback).

> A useful extension would be to pick up changes in forwarded X11
> connections, etc.

This is what I do in my smutt script (which is a screen wrapper for
Mutt).

